I followed your advice with the test case. I made some small changes to it, but by and large it worked great!
Organization-wise, I moved the new test case into the InProcessTransportTest class because I thought that it belonged there. But for this to work, I had to expose the field server in AbstractTransportTest:



      grpc-java/core/src/test/java/io/grpc/internal/AbstractTransportTest.java


        Lines 158 to 161
      in
      2efad75







              * tests in an indeterminate state. 




              */ 




             protected InternalServer server; 




             private ServerTransport serverTransport; 





so that I could set server=null. I had to do this because the after each hook in AbstractTransportTest would try to call server.shutdown if I didnt (which would fail since I dont start that server in the test case).



      grpc-java/core/src/test/java/io/grpc/internal/AbstractTransportTest.java


        Lines 230 to 242
      in
      2efad75







           @After 




           public void tearDown() throws InterruptedException { 




             if (client != null) { 




               client.shutdownNow(Status.UNKNOWN.withDescription("teardown")); 




             } 




             if (serverTransport != null) { 




               serverTransport.shutdownNow(Status.UNKNOWN.withDescription("teardown")); 




             } 




             if (server != null) { 




               server.shutdown(); 




               assertTrue(serverListener.waitForShutdown(TIMEOUT_MS, TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS)); 




             } 




           } 





So I'm not sure whether this was the right move. That being said I'm happy to change it!
And thank you so much for all the help and pointers you've been giving me 🙂

